INSERT INTO `wpds_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2016-07-11 22:11:05','2016-07-11 22:11:05','WordPress is an award-winning web software, used by millions of webmasters worldwide for building their website or blog. SiteGround is proud to host this particular WordPress installation and provide users with multiple resources to facilitate the management of their WP websites:\r\n<h3>Expert <a href=\"http://www.siteground.com/wordpress-hosting.htm\">WordPress Hosting</a></h3>\r\nSiteGround provides superior WordPress hosting focused on speed, security and customer service. We take care of WordPress sites security with unique server-level customizations, WP auto-updates, and daily backups. We make them faster by regularly upgrading our hardware, offering free CDN with Railgun and developing our SuperCacher that speeds sites up to 100 times! And last but not least, we provide real WordPress help 24/7! Learn more about SiteGround WordPress hosting\r\n<h3>Wordpress tutorial and knowledgebase articles</h3>\r\nWordPress is considered an easy to work with software. Yet, if you are a beginner you might need some help, or you might be looking for tweaks that do not come naturally even to more advanced users. SiteGround <a href=\"http://www.siteground.com/tutorials/wordpress/\">WordPress tutorial</a> includes installation and theme change instructions, management of WordPress plugins, manual upgrade and backup creation, and more. If you are looking for a more rare setup or modification, you may visit <a href=\"http://kb.siteground.com\">SiteGround Knowledgebase</a>.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://www.siteground.com/wordpress-hosting/wordpress-themes.htm\">Free WordPress themes</a></h3>\r\nSiteGround experts not only develop various solutions for WordPress sites, but also create unique designs that you could download for free. SiteGround WordPress themes are easy to customize for the particular use of the webmaster.','WordPress Resources at SiteGround','','trash','open','open','','wordpress-resources-at-siteground__trashed','','','2016-10-04 16:29:03','2016-10-04 16:29:03','',0,'',0,'post','',0),(3,2,'2013-08-25 18:09:09','2013-08-26 00:09:09','If you are looking for a wedding in MÃ©xico read carefully the requirements you need for a civil ceremony.\n\nMÃ©xico is part of the Hague Convention which allows the country to issue apostilles valid in all the countries where the Hague convention is valid.\n\nYou can have your coordinator to assist you with all the appropiate paperwork to settle your civil ceremony date. To get married in MÃ©xico you will need teÂ¡he following documents:\n\n<strong>Marriage for foreigners in Mexico</strong>\n\nOriginal and copy of birth certificates, annotated and translated by an authorized translator certified in the Spanish language.\nPrenuptial clinical analyses of both parties for VDRL, HIV, and RH (results are valid for 15 days only). They need to be taken in Mexico, or certified by a Mexican physician.\nCopy of valid passports.\nIf one of the parties is widow or divorced, a certified copy of the decree is required.\nIf one of the parties is minor (18 or younger), identification copy of the parents is needed and they should be presented as witnesses on the ceremony.\nCopy of the tourist visa/immigration slip, received upon arrival in Mexico.\nOriginal and copy of valid passport for two witnesses per party. If they are foreign, they must present a copy of the tourist visa/immigration slip (received upon arrival in Mexico).\nName, age, nationality, home address and occupation of the four witnesses are required as well.\nWitnesses cannot be changed on the certificate.\nThe bride and groom must arrive at least 3 working days prior to the wedding ceremony to submit all the documents.\nThe wedding day, parties and witnesses should not drink any alcohol before the ceremony.\nClients must present a map of the hotel or place where the ceremony is going to be held.\nParties should be presented 20 minutes before the ceremony.\nThey must sign a document where they agree with all the requirements.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-327\" alt=\"1011448_444613788970522_1431166734_n\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2012/10/1011448_444613788970522_1431166734_n.jpg?w=551\" width=\"551\" height=\"367\" />\n\n<strong>Requirements for a marriage between Mexican and Foreigner</strong>\n\nState certificate stating that bride or groom is not married (only for the Mexican to be married).\nBirth certificates of the bride and groom (for the foreign bride or groom, apostled and translated into Spanish by an authorized translator; if the issuing country does not apostle certificates, it must be certified by the Consul of the Mexican Embassy in the country of origin).\nIn case the foreigner does not have a birth certificate, he or she must show a valid passport and fill in an affidavit (given in the Civil Registry).\nCURP (Mexican bride or groom).\nPrenuptial analysis (VDRL, HIV and RH) certified by a doctor (both documents signed, stamped and with the doctorâ€™s professional registration number). Results are valid for 15 days only.\nI.D.s of bride and groom and four witnesses (IFE or valid passport).\nIf either the bride or groom is widowed or divorced, they must show the corresponding certificate.\n\nNote: All documentation should be presented in original form with 2 copies.','Marriage requirements for civil ceremonies in MÃ©xico','','publish','open','open','','marriage-requirements-for-civil-ceremonies-in-mexico','','','2013-08-25 18:09:09','2013-08-26 00:09:09','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=3',0,'post','',0),(5,2,'2012-11-10 21:12:15','2012-11-11 03:12:15','','My Perfect Wedding Riviera Maya','','inherit','open','open','','mpwsignature','','','2012-11-10 21:12:15','2012-11-11 03:12:15','',510,'http://77.104.156.53/~myperf20/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/mpwsignature.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(39,1,'2016-08-01 16:52:55','2016-08-01 16:52:55','[et_pb_section admin_label=\"Se