ypwedding.wordpress.com/2012/11/19/another-one-of-those-roses/',0,'post','',0),(500,2,'2012-11-19 18:31:04','2012-11-20 00:31:04',' ','Mr. and Mrs. - The Wedding of Stephanie and Andrew','','publish','open','open','','mr-and-mrs-the-wedding-of-stephanie-and-andrew','','','2012-11-19 18:31:04','2012-11-20 00:31:04','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/2012/11/19/mr-and-mrs-the-wedding-of-stephanie-and-andrew/',0,'post','',0),(501,2,'2012-12-15 12:07:49','2012-12-15 18:07:49','<p>Wedding Jewelry: StatementÂ NecklacesWhen you decide upon your wedding accessories you have to think of the photo opportunities as well. I know it sounds strange but remember that you will see your wedding pictures for the rest of your life, son you need to have something different and something that will draw attention even after all those years that have passed.Thatâ€™s why I always tell my brides to take a statement necklace with them as well. You can wear it the whole night through and surprise everyone else or you can simply wear it for the photo opportunities, keep it on an hour or two and later passed it to one of your bridesmaids to store. Here are my choices for this week: 1.Ashley Pittman â€“ Mpira Braided-Bead Necklace, Light Horn; 2.kate spade new york â€“ bauble dot long necklace; 3. kate spade â€“ kaleidoscope floral necklace; 4. kate spade â€“ electric gardens necklace; 5. Jose</p><p>via <a href=\'http://fashionbride.wordpress.com/2012/12/15/wedding-jewelry-statement-necklaces/\'>Wedding Jewelry: Statement Necklaces</a>.</p>','Wedding Jewelry: Statement Necklaces','','publish','open','open','','wedding-jewelry-statement-necklaces','','','2012-12-15 12:07:49','2012-12-15 18:07:49','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=121',0,'post','',0),(502,2,'2012-12-27 17:01:58','2012-12-27 23:01:58','Did you know that each year has a specific color? Well 2013 will be colored like a dreamy ocean landscape at Riviera Maya because the color of the year is Â¡EMERALD GREEN! chosen by <a href=\"http://www.pantone.com/pages/pantone/index.aspx\">Pantone</a>\n\nTime Magazine says that \"Every year, Pantone polls designers and brands about colors theyâ€™re featuring to aid in its decision for what hue will tinge the next 12 months. For 2013, the company has bestowed the distinction of Color of the Year on the shade its database identifies as 17-5641: Emerald Green.\" (Article <a href=\"http://newsfeed.time.com/2012/12/10/pantone-names-emerald-as-color-of-the-year-for-2013/\">\"Pantone Names Emerald as Color of The Year for 2013\"</a>)\n\nSo we are glad to show you some colorful ideas for your \"Emerald Destination Wedding\" at our Pinterest board <a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/color-of-the-year-2013/\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/color-of-the-year-2013/\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-171 aligncenter\" alt=\"Emerald green\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2012/12/pic.png?w=551\" width=\"551\" height=\"413\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"></p>\n<b>Grisell Balderas</b> | My Wedding Consultant |\n\nMÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | USA +1 (917) 336 2934 |\n\n<span style=\"color:#cc99ff;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#cc99ff;\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span>Â  |Â  <span style=\"color:#cc99ff;\"><a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#cc99ff;\">grisell@my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span> |','Color of the year 2013','','publish','open','open','','color-of-the-year-2013','','','2012-12-27 17:01:58','2012-12-27 23:01:58','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=126',0,'post','',0),(503,2,'2012-12-24 17:52:15','2012-12-24 23:52:15','<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-134\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-134 alignleft\" alt=\"Venues at Riviera Maya\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2012/12/img_0355-2.jpg?w=200\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Since I lived in Riviera Maya I am surprised on the variety of venues this beautiful destination can offer for a dreamed wedding. ItÂ´s amazing to see pictures of couples getting married every day at this paradise and realize that they had their ceremony or reception in a very unique location worth to be in a cover of a magazine.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Now that you decided to have your wedding at Riviera Maya, the question is how to select the perfect venue that reflects your essence and will bring you the scenery to your perfect destination wedding?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">You can select from a secluded beach ceremony overlooking the amazing turquoise sea of the Caribbean and the magical colors of itÂ´s sunsets, or maybe you prefer an original jungle type venue surrounded by the mangroves.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Here are some things you have to consider to select your perfect venue at Riviera Maya:</p>\n\n<ul style=\"text-align:justify;\">\n	<li>The first thing to think of is the accommodation of your party, you can select between ecological cabins, condos or small properties by the beach, all-inclusive or European plan hotels, the decision depends on several things such as the type of wedding you wish to have, your budget, the size of your wedding party, their ages, the activities you wish to arrange during the wedding experience</li>\n</ul>\n<ul style=\"text-align:justify;\">\n	<li>Another important thing you have to consider while you are choosing the venue is which type of ceremony you prefer, since religious ceremonies not always can be performed at certain locations such as the beach. You can also have a symbolic (non denominational) ceremony performed by a minister or a Mayan ceremony (traditional in the region) performed by a shaman. Once you know which ceremony, you can ask your wedding planner which is the best location according to the type of ceremony you are planning.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul style=\"text-align:justify;\">\n	<li>Riviera Maya is not just beach venues, of course this is the favorite location for a wedding, however you can also find beautiful venues such as ballrooms, open spots with great views of the ocean but not right on the sand, garden areas maybe for a cocktail party or amazing receptions in â€œjungleâ€ style venues surrounded by natural canals.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul style=\"text-align:justify;\">\n	<li>You have to decide if you prefer to have a more â€œnaturalâ€ and â€œgreenâ€ wedding or a more stylish wedding so you can choose your preferred venue. Riviera Maya offers the perfect journey for each coupleÂ´s adventure.</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">These areÂ the most important things to consider on the selection, however each wedding is unique so look for customized wedding options and enjoy your big day in paradise!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Get inspired by our Pinterest images from Riviera Maya click <a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></p>\n<b>Michelle Salazar</b> | My Wedding Coach|\n\nMÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | USA +1 (917) 336 2934 |\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;color:#cc99ff;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\"><span style=\"color:#cc99ff;text-decoration:underline;\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span>Â  |Â  <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;color:#cc99ff;\"><a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#cc99ff;text-decoration:underline;\">michelle@my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span> |','How to choose the perfect venue for your wedding at Riviera Maya','','publish','open','open','','venues-at-riviera-maya','','','2012-12-24 17:52:15','2012-12-24 23:52:15','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=132',0,'post','',0),(504,2,'2013-01-05 11:00:44','2013-01-05 17:00:44','<h2 style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"color:#999999;\">During your â€œDestination Weddingâ€ trip; what will you and your guests do at Riviera Maya?</span></h2>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">We absolutely know that one of your concerns about your Destination Wedding trip is to ENJOY IT! For that reason it is important to plan in advance tours or activities to relax during the stay; of course the purpose of the trip is YOUR wedding so the last you want to see is hangover guests in your big day, or so tired that they need to leave early the reception or, in the worst situation, sick guests; so that is very important to organize those activities after your big day has been celebrated, just in case you require to do it before, we certainly recommend to do it at least 2 days before.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Want some ideas of what to do? Check our most recommended activities to do during your <a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/\" target=\"_blank\">Destination Wedding</a> trip in our Pinterest board <a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/activities-at-riviera-maya/\" target=\"_blank\">â€˜Activities at Riviera Mayaâ€™</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">We take care of everything, yo and your guests just have to choose what you would love to do and we coordinate it.Â Email us to concierge@my-perfectwedding.com</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/activities-at-riviera-maya/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\" wp-image-182 aligncenter\" alt=\"Activities at Riviera Maya\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/blog3.png\" width=\"433\" height=\"528\" /></a></p>\n<b>Grisell Balderas</b> | My Wedding Consultant |\n\nMÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | USA +1 (917) 336 2934 |\n\n<span style=\"color:#9370d8;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span>Â  |Â  <span style=\"color:#9370d8;\"><a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;\">grisell@my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span> |\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"></p>','During your \'Destination Wedding\' trip; what will you and your guests do at Riviera Maya?','','publish','open','open','','activities-at-riviera-maya','','','2013-01-05 11:00:44','2013-01-05 17:00:44','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=157',0,'post','',0),(505,2,'2013-01-15 09:00:56','2013-01-15 15:00:56','<a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-194\" alt=\"Timing\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/154600199677942421_xticoqoj_c.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"359\" /></a>\n\nIf you are planning a beach destination wedding outdoors is very important to take care about the timing for your events considering the sunrise and sunset in each season day so you can plan your ceremony accordingly.\n\nFor sunset ceremonies is always a good idea to begin the ceremony at least 30 min before sunset time starts so the beginning of the ceremony is sunny and at the end you can have beautiful photos with your husband, family and friends with the sunset by the sea or in a beautiful location.\n\nSun set and sunrise are very quick (30 min approximately) so timing is a very important matter. You can find several web pages with tools to know the exact sunset and sunrise time of your wedding day. Here is a good one you can use <a href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/astronomy.html?n=2264\" target=\"_blank\">timeanddate.com</a>\n\n<b>Michelle Salazar</b> | My Wedding Coach|\n\nMÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | USA +1 (917) 336 2934 |\n\n<span style=\"color:#9370d8;\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;text-decoration:underline;\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span>Â  |Â  <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;text-decoration:underline;\">michelle@my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span> |Â </span>','Perfect timing for your ceremony','','publish','open','open','','perfect-timing-for-your-ceremony','','','2013-01-15 09:00:56','2013-01-15 15:00:56','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=193',0,'post','',0),(506,2,'2013-01-24 17:23:37','2013-01-24 23:23:37','Riviera Maya es el destino perfecto para una boda de ensueÃ±o!','','','publish','open','open','','200','','','2013-01-24 17:23:37','2013-01-24 23:23:37','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/2013/01/24/200/',0,'post','',0),(507,2,'2013-01-28 10:00:14','2013-01-28 16:00:14','<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mypwedding\"><img class=\"alignleft\" alt=\"Blog Lunes 28 enero 2013\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/blog-lunes-28-enero-2013.jpg\" width=\"192\" height=\"288\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">If you have already chosen a \'Destination Wedding\' location at the Caribbean this information is specially for you. Thinking about all the important aspects for your wedding is crucial to organize yourself and anticipate to any challenge you may face down at the beach where you will get married. However, you could forget some aspects like the fact that even if you enjoy sunny days and the warm sensation that only a beach can have; you will be wearing a lovely formal dress as well as your boyfriend and guests; and also your hair and makeup must be just perfect that day so we recommend you to seek for local advise regarding this aspect which sometimes is taken for granted. At Riviera Maya all year round you can expect sun and warm weather with an average temperature high of 30Â°C or 86 Â°F. the highest temperatures are registered on May and September when temperatures can reach 32Â°C, 90Â°F. There are also two rainy seasons during October to January and April to July; however they can be a great refresher during the heat of the day.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">We as wedding planners always take care about this topic sharing a lot of tips with brides like these:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:13px;line-height:19px;\">Hiring a local makeup artist is the best option because they know how to </span><span style=\"font-size:13px;line-height:19px;\">maintain</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;line-height:19px;\"> a perfect face of a bride</span></li>\n	<li>Your<span style=\"text-align:justify;font-size:13px;line-height:19px;\"> hair style must be </span><span style=\"text-align:justify;font-size:13px;line-height:19px;\">adequate</span><span style=\"text-align:justify;font-size:13px;line-height:19px;\"> to the humidity level so you must consider this depending on you hair type</span></li>\n	<li>Repellent<span style=\"text-align:justify;font-size:13px;line-height:19px;\"> is necessary between 5 and 7 p.m. because of the humidity and warm sensation mixed up</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">And many other tips that we loved to share with you if you are thinking about getting married at this gorgeous paradise. Please feel free to contact us at concierge@my-perfectwedding.com and let us guide you trough this emotional journey.</p>\n<b>Grisell Balderas</b> | My Wedding Consultant |\n\nMÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | USA +1 (917) 336 2934 |\n\n<span style=\"color:#9370d8;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</span></a>Â  |Â  <a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;\">grisell@my-perfectwedding.com</span></a> |</span>','Weather at Riviera Maya','','publish','open','open','','weather-at-riviera-maya','','','2013-01-28 10:00:14','2013-01-28 16:00:14','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=201',0,'post','',0),(508,2,'2013-02-04 09:50:59','2013-02-04 15:50:59','<h3><span style=\"font-size:1.17em;\">Boys also need wedding tips so we are glad to write this post for men; YES! Maybe you are thinking about how to propose your girlfriend so here are the top 5 tips to inspire you and help you create a very unique proposal for your loved one:</span></h3>\n<a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/engagement-rings/\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-214 alignright\" alt=\"#PoppingTheQuestion\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/post5.png?w=400\" width=\"400\" height=\"551\" /></a>\n<ol>\n	<li><b style=\"font-size:13px;line-height:19px;\">Do something fun and creative:</b><span style=\"font-size:13px;line-height:19px;\">Â The best proposals are always those creative and â€œout of the boxâ€, make it fun by adding a mime during the dinner to deliver the ring box, another idea is to make a T- shirt with the legend â€œShe said yesâ€ with an arrow pointing at her and show it after the proposal so everybody look at you.</span></li>\n	<li><b>Consider her personality:</b>Â  Think about what is important for her, include her loved pet delivering the ring, her preferred color on a flower bouquet, the type of music that she likes during the proposal, important places for her where you can do the proposal or other special interest that will make that moment unique for her.</li>\n	<li><b>Location is important: </b>Select carefully where it will be taking place and once you have your proposal planned talk to the staff, they can always help you with fresh ideas or maybe with some tips they have seen before in their place to achieve the \"wow effect\".</li>\n	<li><b>Surprise her!!! -</b> Making a proposal is like making a surprise party, you have to be very careful with all the details so she cannot have a clue. This is the amazing part of proposals, you can even invite her friends and family during or after the proposal to join you.</li>\n	<li><b>Remember to smile:</b>Â Bring your camera with you, always is a good idea to have the proposal photos or even a film of the event so you can play it to your friends and family or you can even edit this film to be played it during your wedding reception.</li>\n</ol>\nYou can also set up a live-stream channel (on Ustream.com) and invite all your friends and family to watch the proposal live from wherever you choose to propose!\n\nThis is a special occasion for both of you so make of this moment the most emotive one to be remembered and put your best effort to make it unique by asking her with all your love:\n<h4>WOULD YOU MARRY ME?</h4>\n<b>Michelle Salazar</b> | My Wedding Coach|\n\nMÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | USA +1 (917) 336 2934 |\n\n<span style=\"color:#9370d8;\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;text-decoration:underline;\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span>Â  |Â  <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;text-decoration:underline;\">michelle@my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span> |Â </span>','Popping the question: Top 5 tips to propose','','publish','open','open','','top-5-tips-to-propose','','','2013-02-04 09:50:59','2013-02-04 15:50:59','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=213',0,'post','',0),(509,2,'2013-02-11 14:00:44','2013-02-11 20:00:44','<h3 style=\"text-align:justify;\">When I started getting involved in this profession, I thought a Wedding Planner was just the person in charge of the event so it was a great surprise for me to realize that we are much more than that; we actually get involved with the coupleâ€™s dream of their big day that is why weddings are our passion, my business partner and I think that this is more like a hobby that provides us a lot of satisfaction than a just a job. These are the main reasons that I have to consider my job as my favorite hobby:</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mypwedding\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-219 aligncenter\" alt=\"WebsitePic\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/website-pic.png?w=551\" width=\"551\" height=\"349\" /></a></p>\n\n<ol style=\"text-align:justify;\">\n	<li>LOVE!!!: Couples are in love and living in that very emotional stage of a relationship where they smile and enjoy all what is around like if they were living in heaven itself.</li>\n	<li>TRAVEL: When a couple is looking for a Destination Wedding they are expecting the most wonderful vacation of their lives, is not only traveling for pleasure but for the purpose of bonding as one in their favorite place on earth. So I am in charge of becoming their thoughts in something tangible; and as a Iâ€™m living in the chosen city they trust me to put all their request together and be the director â€˜behind the scenesâ€™ of their big day.</li>\n	<li>CHALLENGE: I am used to working on sales and customer service so I thought that my main strength when I became a Wedding Planner would be empathy... I was right when it comes to listening a couple\'s wedding idea and putting all together to make that dream come true, empathy is also our skill when we do our best to search for the right venue and the right supplier that fits the needs of the couple; this is the main challenge we face during the planning process and one of the most satisfying aspects when we accomplish the goal.</li>\n	<li>EMOTION: Since most of our clients are abroad we really need to meet them as much as we can; sometimes when we ask about special requirements, the stories come up and we get to know them better; sometimes is when couples tell us their love story. Any opportunity is great to capture the emotion they have for this unique event; so we are essentially in charge of creating memorable experiences and that is what keep us innovating ourselves.</li>\n	<li>ADVENTURE: This is it! The adventure of a coupleâ€™s lifetime. The big day is coming soon so Bride and Groom are just waiting for that unique moment and the excitement they have is contagious to us; each wedding is an adventure and a new possibility to compose a love story designed only for those lovers; that is one of the aspects that enrich us as wedding planners.</li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">If you would like to schedule an appointment for more ideas about your destination wedding; please send us your request to <a href=\"mailto:concierge@my-perfectwedding.com\">concierge@my-perfectwedding.com</a>Â or contact our skype user \'mypwedding\'. We would be more than glad to assist you during the planning process.</p>\n\n<address><b>Grisell Balderas</b> | My Wedding Consultant |</address><address>MÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | USA +1 (917) 336 2934 |</address><address>My Perfect Wedding Riviera Maya |Â <a title=\"Facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mypwedding\">www.facebook.com/mypwedding</a>Â  |<a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\">\n</a></address>','I am a Destination Wedding Planner becauseâ€¦','','publish','open','open','','destination-wedding-planner','','','2013-02-11 14:00:44','2013-02-11 20:00:44','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=218',0,'post','',0),(510,2,'2013-02-14 12:54:57','2013-02-14 18:54:57','<h2><span style=\"color:#333333;\">Flowers, Chocolates and tons of lovely gifts is the way to show love on Valentine\'s Day!!!Â </span></h2>\n<h3>That is why we thought about BRIDES TO BE so this is our gift for you with all of our affection: \"My Wedding Notebook\" a useful and practical guide to organize your wedding during the planning process.</h3>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><em>CLICK IN THE IMAGE TO DOWNLOAD IT</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"http://db.tt/rcEHHAi8\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-232 aligncenter\" alt=\"My Wedding Notebook\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/my-wedding-notebook.png\" width=\"531\" height=\"426\" /></a></p>\nWe hope you enjoy this gift! And please feel free to contact us if you would like to have a beach wedding at our amazing Riviera Maya, MÃ©xico.\n\n<span style=\"color:#333333;\">Best regards,</span>\n\n<span style=\"color:#333333;\"><b>My Perfect Wedding Staff</b></span>\n\n<span style=\"color:#333333;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#333333;\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span>\n\n<span style=\"color:#333333;\"><a href=\"mailto:concierge@my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#333333;\">concierge@my-perfectwedding.com</span></a></span>\n\n<span style=\"color:#333333;\">MÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062</span>\n\n<span style=\"color:#333333;\"> USA +1 (917) 336 2934</span>','A Valentine\'s Day Gift for you: My Wedding Notebook','','publish','open','open','','my-wedding-notebook','','','2013-02-14 12:54:57','2013-02-14 18:54:57','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=226',0,'post','',0),(511,2,'2013-02-19 09:00:06','2013-02-19 15:00:06','<h2>I am sure you have heard the term â€œTrash the dressâ€ with no idea of what is it; so I want to share with you important information and tips about it...</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/mypwedding\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-238\" alt=\"Trash the dress\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/blog7a.png?w=492\" width=\"344\" height=\"386\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Trash the dress, as the name pronounces is re-using your gown after the wedding day for artistic photography in a different location such as the beach, a â€œcenoteâ€ (subterranean river), fields or another unusual location. Unfortunately this may ruin the dress, so this is a good option for brides that do not want to keep the dress and prefer to have a good memory of it in their pictures. This is a unique adventure but donÂ´t do it if you are considering using again your wedding dress or if itÂ´s very important for you to keep it since it wonÂ´t be the same one after this exciting activity.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">This trend has become very popular after destination weddings since most of them are celebrated in spectacular vacation places that give a very unique sense of originality to the photo.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">If your destination wedding is going to be at the beach, this trend is a great idea to show your inner model and enjoy the wonderful landscape meanwhile the photographer creates amazing pictures of you and your partner.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Consider having light or non make up depending on the place where the photo shooting will be taking place since you may have to go inside the water so the makeup could not be the best once you get out of the water.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Also is very important to carefully select a good photographer with experience in this type of photography, they have the right equipment and the knowledge of the ideal places and light in this special situation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Particularly I love this type of photography since the bride and groom can express themselves away from all their guests. So come to Riviera Maya to live this great experience and keep enjoying your wedding trip after the actual wedding day!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><em>If you would like to schedule an appointment for more ideas about your destination wedding; please send us your request to&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:concierge@my-perfectwedding.com\">concierge@my-perfectwedding.com</a>&nbsp;or contact our skype user â€˜mypweddingâ€™. We would be more than glad to assist you during the planning process.</em></p>\n\n<address><b>Michelle Salazar</b>&nbsp;| Wedding Planner| </address><address>My Perfect Wedding Riviera Maya |&nbsp;<a title=\"Facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mypwedding\">www.facebook.com/mypwedding</a>&nbsp; |</address><address>&nbsp;</address><address><a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-240\" alt=\"Trash the dress - Riviera Maya\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/blog7b.png?w=551\" width=\"551\" height=\"380\" /></a></address>','TRASH THE DRESS: A new Photography trend','','publish','open','open','','trash-the-dress','','','2013-02-19 09:00:06','2013-02-19 15:00:06','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=237',0,'post','',0),(512,2,'2013-03-22 11:00:22','2013-03-22 17:00:22','<h3 style=\"text-align:justify;\">The Mayans are an ancient civilization that lived in Central America for many centuries, they<i> flourished thanks to a deep understanding of the environmental </i><i>conditions that surrounded them; they worshiped the fourth elements:Â  water, fire, earth, air. And their gods blessed them in all their activities through their rituals and ceremonies.</i></h3>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">The Mayans asked for the blessing of their gods in their union ceremonies as well, so love can remain with them for all their lives.Â Come to Riviera Maya and meet the ancient Mayan traditions celebrating your love with the elements of the earth, and let the Shamans give you the godÂ´s blessing through their hands.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">They are three different Mayan ceremonies you can choose from:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><b>Mayan Traditional ceremony</b></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">This ceremony is also called Native. The prayer is recited in the original Mayan with a translation in the required language, in accordance with ancient Mayan traditions.Â â€‹The couple shares the sacred drink of BalchÃ© with the purpose of feeding their souls. They are also blessed with copal smoke, and presented with flower bracelets. These bracelets represent the rings of love.Â Corn and cocoa are offered to the couple. These items are used to signify abundance in the relationship. Bride and groom are united with ribbons.<b>Â </b>Hers has white flower petals, and his has yellow flower petals. These represent the sun and moon, man and woman, and symbolize the union of their lives.</p>\n<a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-249\" alt=\"Mayan1\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/03/mayan1.png\" width=\"396\" height=\"250\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><b>Mayan â€œNew Age ceremonyâ€</b></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">Also calledâ€œNew Ageâ€, as the ceremony is performed with numerous traditions and rituals from Mayans, but also other ancestral cultures<b>.Â </b>â€‹In theÂ centerÂ a candle will represent the fire of love that burns brightly in the heart of the couple, a love that sustains them and also acts as a constant inspiration, example and reminder to friends, family, and the greater world of the way of love, and how to let love guide this new life together. At the end of the ceremony the bride and groom will keep the ceremonial candle and light it in the difficult moments during their relationships, in order to receive wisdom and direction from the guardians when they need such help or further inspiration.</p>\n<a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-250\" alt=\"Mayan2\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/03/mayan2.png\" width=\"415\" height=\"277\" /></a>\n\n<b>PREHISPANIC MAYAN WEDDING</b>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">In this ceremony the Shaman and people helping him during the ritual are dressed as in our Prehispanic Tradition, with feathers andÂ colorfulÂ painting on their bodies.Â Bride and Groom are welcomed and purified by a \"Sahumadora\", a prehispanic dressed woman with a ceremonial censer that burns special healing and protective incense.Â Our professional Mayan Musician can be added to the ceremony in order to have an even better feeling of our traditions.</p>\n<a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/why-us-about-wedding-planners.html\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-251\" alt=\"Mayan3\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/03/mayan3.png\" width=\"451\" height=\"304\" /></a>\n\n<address>Â </address><address><strong><em>Michelle SalazarÂ | My Wedding Coach|</em></strong></address><address><strong><em>MÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | USA +1 (917) 336 2934 |</em></strong></address><address><strong><em>My Perfect Wedding Riviera Maya |Â <a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</a> |</em></strong></address>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\" align=\"center\"><strong><em>With the assistance ofÂ <a href=\"http://www.spiritualityrm.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Spirituality Riviera Maya</a></em></strong></p>','Mayan weddings: a love heritage at Riviera Maya','','publish','open','open','','mayan-weddings-at-riviera-maya','','','2013-03-22 11:00:22','2013-03-22 17:00:22','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=248',0,'post','',0),(513,2,'2013-04-06 10:00:47','2013-04-06 16:00:47','<h3>One of the questions that will come up during the planning of your <span style=\"color:#9370d8;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/services-event-planner-wedding-playa-del-carmen.html\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;\">Destination Wedding</span></a></span> is: What is the dress code for a beach wedding? Maybe you and some of your guests had been in a beach wedding before but there will be still information that you should share with them in order to host your guests in the best way, so this post is dedicated to you in order to simplify your<span style=\"color:#9370d8;\"> <a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/my-wedding-diary-download.html\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;\">â€˜To Do Listâ€™</span></a></span>.</h3>\nThe right name for this code is â€˜Beach Formalâ€™ however is up to you to include terms like: beach chic, semi-formal, cocktail for the evening or even casual if relaxed attire would be allowed. The do\'s and don\'ts must be clear for you so you will be able toÂ adviseÂ your guests what to wear for your wedding:\n\n<strong>Gentlemen Doâ€™s:</strong> Summer suit, Linen shirt, Sleeved shirt, Polo shirt, Linen pants, Khakis, Closed formal shoes and Formal sandals\n\n<strong>Gentlemen Dontâ€™s:</strong> No ties required, Jeans, Flip flops, Shorts, Bermudas, T-shirts or Sneakers\n\n<a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-268\" alt=\"By allaboutjingnjeff\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/by-allaboutjingnjeff.jpg\" width=\"495\" height=\"398\" /></a>\n\n<strong>Women Doâ€™s</strong>: Formal summer sundress, Knee-length skirt, Dressy skirt, Formal sandals and Natural make up\n\n<strong>Women Dontâ€™s</strong>: Cocktail dress, Revealing or skimpy dresses, Wear white or Heels\n\n<a href=\"http://pinterest.com/mypwedding/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-269\" alt=\"By portobellojewelry\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/by-portobellojewelry.jpg?w=551\" width=\"551\" height=\"551\" /></a>\n\nIf you want to receive in your email information related to destination and beach weddings remember to follow this blog.\n\n<b>Grisell Balderas</b> | My Wedding Consultant |\n\nMÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | USA +1 (917) 336 2934 |\n\n<span style=\"color:#9370d8;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</span></a>Â  |Â  <a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\"><span style=\"color:#9370d8;\">grisell@my-perfectwedding.com</span></a> |</span>','Dress code for a Beach Wedding','','publish','open','open','','dress-code-for-a-beach-wedding','','','2013-04-06 10:00:47','2013-04-06 16:00:47','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=256',0,'post','',0),(514,2,'2013-06-24 15:27:21','2013-06-24 21:27:21','Very informative for the brides!','Tips on how to get low-cost bridesmaid dresses','','draft','open','open','','tips-on-how-to-get-low-cost-bridesmaid-dresses-2','','','2013-06-24 15:27:21','2013-06-24 21:27:21','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/2013/06/24/tips-on-how-to-get-low-cost-bridesmaid-dresses-2/',0,'post','',0),(515,2,'2012-12-24 17:44:55','2012-12-24 23:44:55','','Venues at Riviera Maya','','inherit','open','open','','img_0355-2','','','2012-12-24 17:44:55','2012-12-24 23:44:55','',503,'http://77.104.156.53/~myperf20/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/img_0355-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(516,2,'2013-06-24 16:07:17','2013-06-24 22:07:17','<div><p>If you are planning your destination wedding in MÃ©xico and you are planning to ship wedding materials to Mexico through a <b>courier </b>such as <b>UPS, FedEx, DHL</b>, take in consideration the next two points listed below:</p><p>Â </p><p><b>1) Import requirements in Mexico: </b></p><p>Â </p><p>According to Mexican Customs Law, the maximum amount allowed to be imported into Mexico by these companies is US$999.99 per shipment. If the value of the shipment is US$1,000.00 or more, the consignee will automatically be considered a regular importer and will be required to have an <b>Import License (Tax ID number in Mexico)</b>. Customs considers the commercial value to determine duties and/or taxes, so in the case the value is declared null or very low, Customs authorities may give a minimum commercial value considering the kind of item, country of origin and manufacture.</p><p>Â </p><p><b>- Hotels in Mexico Do Not have the appropriate Import License to assume responsibility of the permanent or temporary imports of their guests. </b></p><p><b>- Resorts are usually not allowed to pay import taxes for the imports of their guests, as they are not tax-deductible. </b></p><p style=\"text-align:center;\">Â <a href=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/mexico-map1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image aligncenter\" id=\"i-289\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/mexico-map1.jpg?w=500\" width=\"500\" height=\"348\" /></a></p><p><b>2)Restricted Products: </b></p><p>Â </p><p>Regardless the shipment values, the products listed below are subject to <b>import restrictions </b>pursuant Mexican law. In such cases an Import License will be mandatory to clear customs, also itÂ´s a lengthy process to obtain the appropriate permits. If you are planning to ship some of the following products, itÂ´s better to contact a broker to send them so you can get your items in time; also a broker can let you know if itÂ´s possible or not to send the items.</p><p>Â </p></div><div><p>1. Ceramic / Porcelain articles: Pottery, dishes, crockery, cups, pepper/salt shakers, etc.</p><p>2. Sand &amp; Seashells</p><p>3. Food and perishables</p><p>4. Wines, beverages and any liquid</p><p>5. Clothes and textiles</p><p>6. Sandals and Footwear</p><p>7. Products made in China (high taxes)</p><p>8. First aid kits and medicines</p><p>9. Suntan lotions, creams and gels</p><p>10. Wood products and wood packaging</p><p>11. Candles</p><p>12. Used clothes and personal effects</p><p>13. Lighters and matches</p><p>14. Sparklers / Fireworks</p><p>15. Repellents and Insecticides</p><p>17. Toys, beach balls and balloons</p><p><b>Important: </b>High restricted materials are not limited to this list. Here we are listing the most common products we have identified with high taxes or pre-requisites applied.</p></div><p><em>This information was provided by:Â <a href=\"http://www.exhibitionscargo.com/\">http://www.exhibitionscargo.com/</a></em></p><p>Â </p><p><b>Michelle Salazar</b>Â | My Wedding Coach |</p><p><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</a>Â  |<a href=\"http://michelle@my-perfectwedding.com\"> michelle@my-perfectwedding.com</a>Â |</p><p>Â </p>','Shipping your wedding items to MÃ©xico','','publish','open','open','','shipping-your-wedding-items-to-mexico','','','2013-06-24 16:07:17','2013-06-24 22:07:17','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=283',0,'post','',0),(517,2,'2013-07-01 10:13:00','2013-07-01 16:13:00',' ','Social Media and Your Blog','','publish','open','open','','social-media-and-your-blog','','','2013-07-01 10:13:00','2013-07-01 16:13:00','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/2013/07/01/social-media-and-your-blog/',0,'post','',0),(518,2,'2013-07-06 13:00:11','2013-07-06 19:00:11','<b>One of the biggest decisions during the planning process is to choose the song you will be dancing when you are announced as bride and groom.</b>\n\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-307 alignright\" alt=\"BRENDA &amp; JUAN JOSE-51\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/brenda-juan-jose-51.jpg?w=551\" width=\"551\" height=\"367\" />\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">You may consider a special song you share with your couple, but if you do not have one here are some ideas we share of our favorite love songs that could be used as a first dance.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:justify;\">The importance of the first dance is that you and your loved one share a special moment when you can finally relax after all the planning and begin enjoying your wedding and the rest of your lifeÂ´s together.</p>\nWe hope you can find the perfect song that express what you have to say to each other:\n\n<b>1. Bruno Mars </b>â€“ Marry you\n\n<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OMr9zCvtOfY\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OMr9zCvtOfY</a>\n\n<b>2. Barry White</b> â€“ Just the way you are\n\n<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XF8ZRjfGACA\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XF8ZRjfGAC</a>\n\n<b>3. Frank Sinatra</b> - The Way You Look Tonight\n\n<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1gab2Vuz2Nk\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1gab2Vuz2Nk</a>\n\n<strong>4.</strong>Â <strong>Jason Mraz â€“ Lucky</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=acvIVA9-FMQ\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=acvIVA9-FMQ</a>\n\n<b>5. Ellie Goulding</b>Â  - Your Song\n\n<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D9AFMVMl9qE\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D9AFMVMl9qE</a>\n\n<b>6. Counting Crows </b>â€“ Accidentally in love\n\n<b>7. Aqualung</b> â€“ Brighter than sunshine\n\n<b>8. Michael BublÃ©</b> â€“ Everything\n\n<b>9. Beyonce</b>Â  - Love On Top\n\n<b>10. Frank Sinatra</b> - Fly Me To The Moon\n\n<b>11. Extreme</b> -Â  More Than Words\n\n<b>12. Snow Patrol</b>Â  - Just Say Yes\n\n<b>13. Barry White</b>Â  - You\'re The First, The Last, My Everything\n\n<strong>14.Â Â  </strong><b>Snow Patrol</b> - Chasing Cars\n\n<b>15. Jason Mraz</b>- I am only yours\n\n<strong>16. Elvis</strong><strong> â€“ </strong>Canâ€™t Help Falling In Love\n\n<strong>17. Kings of Leon</strong><strong> â€“ </strong>Use Somebody\n\n<strong>18. Dido</strong><strong> â€“ </strong>Thank you\n\n<strong>19. Hoobastank</strong><strong> â€“ </strong>The Reason\n\n<strong>20. Jack Johnson</strong><strong> â€“ </strong>Better Together\n\n<strong>21. Etta James</strong><strong> â€“ </strong>At Last\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>22. Michael Bubble</strong><strong> - </strong>Dream a Little Dream of Me\n\n<b>23. Wonderwall</b> â€“ Oasis\n\n<b>24. You Make It Real</b> - James Morrison\n\n<b>25. Iris</b> - The Goo Goo Dolls\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Michelle Salazar</b> | My Wedding Coach|\n\nMÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | Cel: (044) 984 133 33 50 |\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\">\nwww.my-perfectwedding.com</a></span>Â  |Â  <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\">michelle@my-perfectwedding.com</a></span> |\n&nbsp;','Our 25 favorite love songs for the first dance','','publish','open','open','','our-25-favorite-love-songs-for-the-first-dance','','','2013-07-06 13:00:11','2013-07-06 19:00:11','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=304',0,'post','',0),(519,2,'2013-07-24 17:31:43','2013-07-24 23:31:43','<b>The sand ceremony is becoming more and more popular in symbolic and also religious ceremonies since itÂ´s a short ceremony that can be added to the actual ceremony and offers a nice symbol of the unity of marriage and the beginning of a new â€œtogetherâ€ of the couple.</b>\n\n<b>Â <a href=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/sandceremonyvases.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image aligncenter\" id=\"i-315\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/07/sandceremonyvases.jpg?w=422\" /></a></b>\n\nDuring the sand ritual, the bride and the groom both pour sand from individual containers, which represent their individual selves, into a third, common vessel. This symbolizes the two coming together in a way that cannot be separated. The sand can be different colors (it can be the wedding colors) one for the bride and one for the groom so they can pour their sand at a time creating layers. In the end the common vassel will become a piece of art giving the couple a beautiful reminder of their new life together that can take home and decorate their home.\n\nDuring the sand ceremony ritual the couple can exchange their vows; a song or poem can be played in the background or even the minister can talk about love. Anything that can make even more special this moment for both of them.\n\n<b>DIY Sand ceremony </b>\n\nThis idea is not only a very symbolic and loving trend but also can be a DIY project and itÂ´s a cheap idea to include in your wedding ceremony.\n\nThe sand can be found in almost all colors or it can be painted with your favorite color.\n\nVases can be found in different shapes, if you are having a destination wedding consider that the vases are not too big so you can take them back home without paying extra for more baggage.\n\n<b>Michelle Salazar</b> | My Wedding Coach|\n\nMÃ©x +52 (984) 877 8062 | Cel: (044) 984 133 33 50 |\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</a></span>Â  |Â  <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\">michelle@my-perfectwedding.com</a></span> |','How to include a Sand ceremony in your wedding','','publish','open','open','','how-to-include-a-sand-ceremony-in-your-wedding','','','2013-07-24 17:31:43','2013-07-24 23:31:43','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=313',0,'post','',0),(520,2,'2013-11-21 18:10:55','0000-00-00 00:00:00','When you are in the wedding planning you need a time to relax after a long day at work and all the stress that comes with the details of the wedding so here is a short list of <strong>10 MUST see</strong> love / wedding movies of all times, you can even see some details that you will like to incorporate to your wedding. So keep the popcorn nearby and enjoy the show!\n\n1.<strong> The father of the bride</strong> A common situation when the father is not\n\n<strong>2. The Notebook</strong> is an all time favorite of everyone who loves romantic movies. This touching love story is not a wedding story but is for sure a love story that will make your heart melt!\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-324\" alt=\"thenotebook-movieposter1\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/08/thenotebook-movieposter1.jpg?w=551\" width=\"551\" height=\"814\" />','10 Love movies you must see when you are planning your wedding','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-11-21 18:10:55','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=323',0,'post','',0),(521,2,'2014-08-22 08:30:30','2014-08-22 14:30:30','<strong>Beach weddings are now a days very popular.</em> If you like the idea of getting married at a destination wedding on a beach location you have to consider the fact that beach places are usually very windy and a short or long veil will not be very comfortable for you and may ruin some of your wedding photos. \n\nI have seen lots of weddings where the bride look stunning but at the end the wind makes itÂ´s move and blow up the veil distracting also the guests that are looking the veil instead of the beautiful bride.\n\nWe have seen lots of photos with brides wearing long veils by the beach and the veil looks amazing. This look takes a lot of effort from the photographer but at the end makes a great pic. </strong>\n\n<img src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2014/08/fine-art-studio-g026.jpg\" alt=\"Fine Art Studio G026\" width=\"290\" height=\"280\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-367\" />\n\nThen I will recommend to use a different option instead of the veil for the ceremony and before or after the ceremony some photo poses with your veil on. An option instead of the veil can be a head piece like a tiara or a tropical flower on a side will look amazing and will make a great touch for your beach look.\n\nPhoto by Fine Art studio www.fineartstudiomexico.com/\n\nMichelle Salazar | My Wedding Coach|\nmichelle@my-perfectwedding.com | www.my-perfectwedding.com ','Veil for a beach wedding','','publish','open','open','','veil-for-a-beach-wedding','','','2014-08-22 08:30:30','2014-08-22 14:30:30','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=329',0,'post','',0),(522,2,'2013-11-21 18:09:23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<h3>Mexico is safer than other popular destinations.</h3>\n<div>Mexico, one of the worldâ€™s great travel destinations, is often singled out for violent crimeÂ without telling the whole story. While there is sporadic violence along parts of the U.S.Â border, the majority of Mexicoâ€™s key tourism areas are not only safe, but safer than manyÂ other popular tourism areas.Â <b>Â <a href=\"http://howsafeismexico.com/international_murder_rates.html\">COMPARE POPULAR TRAVEL DESTINATIONS &gt;</a></b></div>\n<h3>The Yucatan is as safe as rural U.S. states.</h3>\n<div>The magnificent beaches and ancient ruins of the Mexican State of Yucatan are among theÂ safest and most spectacular resort beaches in the world. Yucatanâ€™s low homicide rate isÂ lower than the rural U.S. States of Wyoming, Montana, Oregon and North Dakota, WestÂ Virginia and several others.Â Â <a href=\"http://howsafeismexico.com/6.html\">COMPARE U.S. CITIES TO MEXICO &gt;</a></div>\n<div><b>\n</b><b>Read more of this article on:Â <a href=\"http://howsafeismexico.com/index.html\">http://howsafeismexico.com/index.html</a></b></div>\n<a href=\"http://howsafeismexico.com/6.html\">http://howsafeismexico.com/6.html</a>','How safe is MÃ©xico?','','draft','open','open','','','','','2013-11-21 18:09:23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=331',0,'post','',0),(523,2,'2013-10-11 09:04:43','2013-10-11 15:04:43',' ','11things you need to consider when choosing location for your DW','','publish','open','open','','11things-you-need-to-consider-when-choosing-location-for-your-dw','','','2013-10-11 09:04:43','2013-10-11 15:04:43','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/2013/10/11/11things-you-need-to-consider-when-choosing-location-for-your-dw/',0,'post','',0),(524,2,'2013-11-23 10:57:36','2013-11-23 16:57:36','<h3><em><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Welcome bags are the most trendy way to say \"thank you for travelling\" to your guests in a destination wedding.</span></em></h3>\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\">A welcome bag can be as expensive as you prefer depending on your budget. To stay in budget I suggest to ask a local wedding planner or supplier to purchase, assemble and deliver the bags for you, tis way you will not be carrying extra lugagge and you can have local products that can be fun for your guests to try.</span>\n<h4><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-339\" alt=\"1456001_549178608498831_235230801_n\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/11/1456001_549178608498831_235230801_n.jpg?w=300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></span></h4>\n<span style=\"line-height:1.5;color:#000000;\">If you are planning a beach wedding below is a list of products you can consider to include in your welcome bag:</span>\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Sun block and / or sun tan</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Sandals</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Bottle waterÂ </span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Snacks</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Local art crafts or souvenirs</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Post cards of the place you are visiting</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Itinerary of the trip (events, venues, et )</span></li>\n</ul>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-337\" alt=\"855fd30c2d52079e011ef4ae664ddb6c\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2013/11/855fd30c2d52079e011ef4ae664ddb6c.jpg\" width=\"236\" height=\"354\" />\n\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\">You can personalize all the items with your couple`s logo and you can also prefer a basket instead of a bag, depending on the items you are including.</span>\n\n<address><b>Michelle Salazar</b> | My Wedding Coach|</address><address>Mex +52 (984) 877 8062 | Cel 044 984 133 3350 |</address><address><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</a></span>Â  |Â  <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\">michelle@my-perfectwedding.com</a></span> |</address><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><b>Â </b></span>','What to include in a welcome bag for a beach wedding','','publish','open','open','','what-to-include-in-a-welcome-bag-for-a-beach-wedding','','','2013-11-23 10:57:36','2013-11-23 16:57:36','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=336',0,'post','',0),(525,2,'2014-10-27 08:00:01','2014-10-27 14:00:01','<em>If you are having a destination wedding and just started the planning you will find tons of flower and decor, cake and general style pictures for your wedding on the web you will fall in love with and as soon as you find the right one that fits your wedding style it will be very difficult to change your mind specially in terms of decor and flowers, that is why our suggestion is to start your research first learning about the place you are getting married, the weather, size of the venues, style of the venues and any other useful information that can help you visualize first what will be the best to include on your destination wedding. A wedding planner can assist you getting the correct suppliers, and giving you more information and the best options to create what you are envisioning and will save you a lot of time, money and decisions.</em>\n\nTalking about flowers it\'s very important to know wich flowers are local in the destination you will have your wedding so you can take advantage of the natural beauty of the place and you also get better deals to keep your event in budget. Learning the local flowers is very important since they are places where is very difficult &nbsp;to find flowers you are used to because the weather is different which makes foreign flowers more expensive and more difficult to handle.\n\n<img src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2014/10/vanessaseumas_t_0041.jpg?w=551\" alt=\"Vanessa+Seumas_T_0041\" width=\"551\" height=\"367\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-377\" />\n\nTalking about the decor also the weather is very important issue to consider, if it\'s a rainy season you should consider a closed area or keep in mind to have a back up plan in case of rain. If it\'s a windy season the decor should be planned accordingly as well avoiding items that can fly away from the tables and if you are planning to have candles a good idea in this case is preferring LED candles instead (not the same look but if they are covered look good).\n\nHiring a professional wedding planner that is familiar with the destination you are getting married is the best idea since he/she will know what will be better to create the dreamed event you are looking for, even if it\'s raining. \n\nIf you need assistance in Cancun, and the Riviera Maya, Mexico, contact us at concierge@my-perfectwedding.com\n\nPhoto by: Del Sol Photography\n\n<strong>Michelle Salazar | My Wedding Coach| michelle@my-perfectwedding.com</strong>\n \n','The perfect flowers and decor for your destination wedding','','publish','open','open','','the-perfect-flowers-and-decor-for-your-destination-wedding','','','2014-10-27 08:00:01','2014-10-27 14:00:01','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=348',0,'post','',0),(526,2,'2014-02-24 09:20:54','2014-02-24 15:20:54','<h2>Ready to tie the knot in the beautiful Mexico? Your destination wedding is not complete until you include one of this fun Mexican cocktails that will make the difference and will enhace the Mexican ambiance. Â¡Si seÃ±or!</h2>\n<h3>Tamarind Margarita</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-358\" alt=\"images\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2014/02/images.jpg\" width=\"194\" height=\"259\" />\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:1.17em;line-height:1.5em;\">Ingredients:</span></h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>4 oz blanco tequila</li>\n	<li>3 oz Â tamarind concentrate</li>\n	<li>1 oz simple syrup</li>\n	<li>chili powder for rimming</li>\n	<li>1 cup ice</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Preparation:</strong></h4>\n<ol>\n	<li>Pour the ice, tequila, tamarind concentrate and simple syrupÂ into a blender.</li>\n	<li>Blend until smooth.</li>\n	<li>RimÂ a chilled margarita glassÂ with chili powder.</li>\n	<li>Pour the blended contents into the glass.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Flaming Mexican Flag</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-355\" alt=\"ac7736ae41a416eed0bc36d80638f7c5\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2014/02/ac7736ae41a416eed0bc36d80638f7c5.jpg\" width=\"236\" height=\"236\" />\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>1/2 oz white tequila</li>\n	<li>1/2 oz grenadine syrup</li>\n	<li>1/2 oz green creme de menthe</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Preparation:</h4>\n<ol>\n	<li>Layer into a 2 oz. shooter: grenadine, then creme de menthe, tequila.</li>\n	<li>Light on fire</li>\n	<li>then blow out and slam.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>GingerÂ´s lost Island</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-356\" alt=\"2011-cocktails-gingers-island\" src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2014/02/2011-cocktails-gingers-island.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"250\" />\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n	<li>Pinch of cinnamon</li>\n	<li>1 1/4 ounces ginger liqueur</li>\n	<li>2 cardamom pods</li>\n	<li>1 apple wedge, cut into thin slices and fanned, for garnish</li>\n	<li>1 1/4 ounces mezcal</li>\n	<li>1/2 ounce fresh lime juice</li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height:1.5em;\">1/2 ounce apple juice</span></li>\n	<li>1/4 ounce agave nectar</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Preparation:</h4>\n<ol>\n	<li>In a cocktail shaker, lightly crush the cardamom.</li>\n	<li>Add ice and all of the remaining ingredients except the garnish and shake well.</li>\n	<li>Pour through a fine strainer into an ice-filled double rocks glass.</li>\n	<li>Garnish with the apple fan.</li>\n</ol>\n&nbsp;\n<h2>Salud!</h2>\n<address><b>Michelle Salazar</b>Â | My Wedding Coach|</address><address><span style=\"line-height:1.5em;\">My Perfect Wedding Riviera Maya |Â </span><a style=\"line-height:1.5em;\" title=\"Facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mypwedding\">www.facebook.com/mypwedding</a><span style=\"line-height:1.5em;\">Â  |</span></address>','3 Original MEXICAN cocktails for your destination wedding','','publish','open','open','','3-original-mexican-cocktails-for-your-destination-wedding','','','2014-02-24 09:20:54','2014-02-24 15:20:54','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=353',0,'post','',0),(527,2,'2014-09-06 08:30:32','2014-09-06 14:30:32','Mexican weddings include cultural / religious traditions and you may like some of this traditions to include in your own wedding if you are having a destination wedding in MÃ©xico, have relatives from MÃ©xico or simply you are a MÃ©xico fan.\n\n<img src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2014/08/brenda-juan-jose-73.jpg?w=551\" alt=\"BRENDA &amp; JUAN JOSE-73\" width=\"551\" height=\"367\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-374\" />\n\n<strong>1. \"Vibora de la Mar\"</strong>\nThis is a Mexican child song and in Mexican weddings when the song starts one of the bridesmaids will ask other girls to joing her and start marching around all the reception area following the song, at the end of the song all girls gathers on the dance floor and the bride throught the bouquet. The boys do the same after the girls and the groom throughts the wedding garter.\n\n<strong>2. Including a Mexican attire as your second dress or for the bridesmaids</strong>\nThis is nice and different touch, they are several traditional dresses (depending of the area in MÃ©xico) and some of them are really unique pieces of art, most of them are handmade so they can be tailor made.\n\n<strong>3.Flower bouquet on your curch wedding for virgen Mary</strong>\nIf you are catholic you may include in your church wedding an extra bouquet and at the end of the ceremony give it away together with your husband to the virgin Mary. In MÃ©xico she is the symbol of a wife that takes care of the hoem and will bless your marriage \n\nPhoto by http://www.rodelrio.com/\n\nMichelle Salazar | My Wedding Coach|\nmichelle@my-perfectwedding.com |www.my-perfectwedding.com  |  \n','3 Mexican wedding traditions you will love','','publish','open','open','','3-mexican-wedding-traditions-you-will-love','','','2014-09-06 08:30:32','2014-09-06 14:30:32','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=366',0,'post','',0),(528,2,'2014-08-30 09:00:59','2014-08-30 15:00:59','When you start planning your wedding is very common to look around on the social media, in pages like Pinterest, Loverly, etc. that are very useful to inspire us. \n\nHowever when talking about flowers is very important to know first the place you are having your wedding (if itÂ´s a destination wedding) and start learning which flowers are local in that place so you can look for inspiration whith that particular type of flowers.\n\nWhy is so important to have local flowers? You can save a lot of money if the flowers are not from other place where they need to be shipped from; also you will help the environment lowering down the carbon footprint of your wedding by consuming what is local on the destination you are having your wedding. And the most important is that the local flowers will blend perfectly with the nature you have around.\n\n<img src=\"http://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2014/08/2014-05-17-16-48-54.jpg\" alt=\"2014-05-17 16.48.54\" width=\"479\" height=\"512\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-370\" />\n\nThree local flowers in the Riviera Maya (Cancun, Playa del Carmen, Tulum) are: gerbers, roses and lilys (not callas)\n\nso with this in mind consider what type of flowers you will have for your decor and personal flowers.\n\nMichelle Salazar | My Wedding Coach|\nmichelle@my-perfectwedding.com | www.my-perfectwedding.com\n\n\n','Tropical flowers for your beach wedding in MÃ¨xico','','publish','open','open','','tropical-flowers-for-your-beach-wedding-in-mexico','','','2014-08-30 09:00:59','2014-08-30 15:00:59','',0,'http://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=369',0,'post','',0),(529,2,'2015-01-28 12:19:09','2015-01-28 18:19:09','<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong>Planning a destination wedding at the beach is a great adventure and a trully enjoyable exerience. To make sure you take advantage of the great ambience the beach / outdoor give us we need to ensure you can have the perfect lightning of an outdoor wedding to enjoy the landscape but avoiding the sun and hot weather of the beach.Â </strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/patrickanh_w_0253.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-382 aligncenter\" src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/patrickanh_w_0253.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Patrick+Anh_W_0253\" width=\"391\" height=\"266\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">Photo credit: Del Sol Photography</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">So, how to start planning a productive timeline to have the perfect lightning for pictures at the ceremoy. Here are some advices to create your wedding schedule:</p>\n<strong>1. Hair and make up</strong> time depends on starting time of the photography session and also how many bridesmaids are you having on the getting ready, but consider aprox 2-3hrs until you are ready with your dress on!\n\n<strong>2. Photoshooting</strong> time also depends on how many pictures you want to have prior the ceremony. Some couples prefer to have just pictures of both at their \"first look\" and will only take aprox 1-2hrs but if you are having a big bridal party and want to include all of them in the pre phtoshooting consider at least 3hrs\n\n<a href=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/18d3d23ec91767103d10618ed828074f.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-384 aligncenter\" src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/01/18d3d23ec91767103d10618ed828074f.jpg?w=200\" alt=\"18d3d23ec91767103d10618ed828074f\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">Photo credit: Katie Lopez Photography</p>\n<strong>3. Ceremony</strong> time must be at least 30min before sunset so the photographer can capture the sundown at the end of the ceremony (great pics!) Ceremonies last 15-30min aprox\n\n<strong>4. Cockatil</strong> must follow the ceremony time, consider 1hr for cocktail.\n\n<strong>5. Reception</strong> must follow the cocktail and the duration of the reception depends on you and your guests. I should say 3hrs minimum for the reception.\n\nOf course every wedding is unique and you can always innovate and create a unique wedding. Tell us how are you planning your wedding timeline.\n\n<strong>Michelle Salazar</strong> | My Wedding Coach|\n\n<a href=\"http://www.my-perfectwedding.com/\">www.my-perfectwedding.com</a>Â  |Â  <a href=\"mailto:grisell@my-perfectwedding.com\">michelle@my-perfectwedding.com</a> |','5 steps to create your wedding timeline for a beach wedding','','publish','open','open','','5-steps-to-create-your-wedding-timeline-for-a-beach-wedding','','','2015-01-28 12:19:09','2015-01-28 18:19:09','',0,'https://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=381',0,'post','',0),(530,2,'2015-04-21 09:04:35','2015-04-21 16:04:35','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>We talked with the image consultant Paty Burgos of 30 segundos about important makeup tips for our brides, so you can look amazing on your wedding day, here some pointers</strong>:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">* Make sure you have your trial at least three weeks prior your wedding day. If you plan on using fake tan for that day, have a test run before your makeup trial so that your makeup artist can see what color your skin becomes with the tan.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">* Prepare with photos you can show to your makeup artist to have an idea of what you want.</p>\r\n* Avoid wearing a foundation with SPF. Many formulas now include sun protection, which is wonderful for your everyday look. But on your wedding day, stick to a traditional foundation. The reason is that some ingredients in the SPF formulas can cause the face to look white in flash photography.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">* Wedding makeup should last as long as you do; so be sure to use long lasting and waterproof foundations, concealers, lip and eye products.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">* Another basic rule is to have a touch-up makeup kit during the ceremony and the wedding party . Make sure you have a small bag with the basics such as face powder, blot papers, eyeliner , lipstick and concealer.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So, ladies makeup is very important to have perfect photos on your wedding day.</p>\r\nFor more makeup tips contact Pty Burgos: http://www.30segundos.com.mx/\r\n\r\nMy Perfect Wedding\r\nconcierge@my-perfectwedding.com\r\nwww.my-perfectwedding.com','Bridal Makeup tips to look flawless on your big day.','','publish','open','open','','bridal-makeup-tips-to-look-flawless-on-your-big-day','','','2016-10-04 16:30:39','2016-10-04 16:30:39','',0,'https://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=420',0,'post','',0),(531,2,'2015-04-29 15:28:06','2015-04-29 22:28:06','A common situation is having kids at your wedding weekend so, let\'s plan activities and fun ideas for them so they feel included on the weekend festivities as well.\r\n\r\n* A fun idea is sending evening amenities to kids rooms. My personal favorite is cookies with milk, you can personalized the containers with your wedding logo\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-431\" src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/2b5b55e1a51ac52333015ea6fc9b7a48.jpg\" alt=\"2b5b55e1a51ac52333015ea6fc9b7a48\" width=\"236\" height=\"354\" />\r\n\r\n* Include the kid\'s on your wedding ceremony as flower girl or ring bearer. They can bring cute signs and outfits.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-432\" src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/89f7c4732c6473c7338723be0ae45a9a.jpg\" alt=\"89f7c4732c6473c7338723be0ae45a9a\" width=\"236\" height=\"332\" />\r\n\r\n* How about cool escort cards for the kids with lego or other mini toy or use the lego as centerpiece for kids to have fun building.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-433\" src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/8fccadfaf62ec3247123bb2b180e4962.jpg\" alt=\"8fccadfaf62ec3247123bb2b180e4962\" width=\"236\" height=\"354\" />\r\n\r\n* Set up a table specially for the kids (preferably near their parents) with very colorful items.\r\n\r\n*Include on the table set up a coloring kit with crayons, paints and other fun stuff. Label the items for them to know their places.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-434\" src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/46c00007bc47bd1961f08ed6f47c1828.jpg?w=560\" alt=\"46c00007bc47bd1961f08ed6f47c1828\" width=\"560\" height=\"841\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-436\" src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/0d343b7d8672b62b27f106e32e3cf9b5.jpg?w=560\" alt=\"0d343b7d8672b62b27f106e32e3cf9b5\" width=\"560\" height=\"839\" />\r\n\r\n* Don\'t forget to include kids on your wedding photos!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-437\" src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/04/a1dafd2362113b510f2dcd39f55f7bec.jpg\" alt=\"a1dafd2362113b510f2dcd39f55f7bec\" width=\"480\" height=\"720\" />\r\n\r\nAnd enjoy your wedding as a kid!!!!\r\n\r\nFor more cool ideas follow our \"Just for Kids\" pinterest board: https://www.pinterest.com/mypwedding/kids/\r\n\r\nMy Perfect Wedding\r\nwww.my-perfectwedding.com\r\nconcierge@my-perfectwedding.com','How to Include kids on your wedding','','publish','open','open','','how-to-include-kids-on-your-wedding','','','2016-10-04 16:30:28','2016-10-04 16:30:28','',0,'https://mypwedding.wordpress.com/?p=430',0,'post','',0),(532,2,'2015-07-14 10:09:15','2015-07-14 17:09:15','Ilumination is a very important aspect of the decor for a wedding reception, it gives the feel you want and the Wow efect your guests will love.\r\n\r\nA must for a wedding decor specially if you are looking for a romantic style is the candle light. It will totally chage the scene when you include it on your reception recor, here are some ideas how you can include it for your wedding:\r\n\r\n* Hanging from trees, ceillings, walls or as backdrop. This idea will open spaces and gives a great feel of a whole ambience not only the tables.\r\n\r\n* In the centerpieces and as table decor. We always include at least a couple of candles on all table decor if the wedding is on the evening, it will help create an intimate space on your wedding table and will enhace your floral or centerpieces. Lanterns are also a very popular choice for table decor, use small lanters for this prupose so everyone in the table can see each other.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-449\" src=\"https://mypwedding.files.wordpress.com/2015/07/rachelglenn-0577.jpg?w=560\" alt=\"RachelGlenn-0577\" width=\"560\" height=\"842\" />\r\n\r\n* As ambience decor. You can use floating candles on a pool, lanterns on a walk way or even tiki torches to give a tropical feel to your destination wedding. Keep the candles away from the people to avoid any incident.\r\n\r\n* As a give 